description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Band 5 Chemotherapy Nurses to join our team at WhittingtonHealth Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have continuing responsibility for the nursing care given to individual patients, at times, without direct supervision. You will be personally accountable for the nursing standards of such delegated duties. They will also be responsible for demonstrating procedures to qualified and/or unqualified staff, thus facilitating learning. You will provide evidence based care, advice and information to patients and their relatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your main duties will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Planning the delivery, implementing and evaluating patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver a high standard of comprehensive skilled and evidence based nursing care to patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist patients, carers and their families to identify health and well-being goals as part of the Living with and Beyond Cancer strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately record observations and changes in patients’ conditions and report back to the responsible nurse in charge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in planning and implementing methods of rehabilitation for patients and their carers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current NMC Registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 months experience in a similar role with NHS setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are the person for this role please apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
